2026-05-16 23:15:28 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #6 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_code({"code": "import pandas as pd, numpy as np, re, glob, os, math\npaths = glob.glob(os.environ['SANDBOX_DIR'] + '/kramabench-environment-hard-8/files/*beach_datasheet.csv')\n# keep only expected 8\nkeep_names = [\n'city_point_beach_datasheet.csv','m_street_beach_datasheet.csv','pleasure_bay_and_castle_island_beach_datasheet.csv',\n'carson_beach_datasheet.csv','malibu_beach_datasheet.csv','tenean_beach_datasheet.csv','wollaston_beach_datasheet.csv','constitution_beach_datasheet.csv'\n]\npaths = [p for p in paths if os.path.basename(p) in keep_names]\n\ndef parse_enterococcus(val):\n    if pd.isna(val):\n        return np.nan\n    s=str(val).strip()\n    if s=='':\n        return np.nan\n    # handle forms like '<,10' or '<,20' from CSV mis-splitting\n    # sometimes Enterococcus column split yields two columns: one contains '<' and next number.\n    # We'll handle numeric or comma-separated patterns.\n    if re.fullmatch(r'-?\\d+(\\.\\d+)?', s):\n        return float(s)\n    # if contains comma, take last numeric token\n    nums=re.findall(r'-?\\d+(?:\\.\\d+)?', s)\n    if nums:\n        return float(nums[-1])\n    return np.nan\n\nfailed_total=0\nfailed_and_pos1day=0\n\nfor p in sorted(paths):\n    df=pd.read_csv(p, header=None, dtype=str)\n    # Identify data rows: first column starts with date like \"August\" or \"September\"\n    first_col=df.iloc[:,0].astype(str)\n    mask=first_col.str.contains(r'^(\"?)(January|February|March|April|May|June|July|August|September|October|November|December)', regex=True)\n    data=df[mask].copy()\n    if data.empty:\n        continue\n    # Determine column indices for 1-Day Rain and Enterococcus values.\n    # From previews, columns: Date, 1-Day Rain, 2-Day Rain, 3-Day Rain, (Tag,Enterococcus) possibly repeated.\n    # In CSV, there may be extra empty columns at start; but in these files, date row begins at col 0.\n    # We'll extract 1-Day Rain from col 1.\n    rain1=data.iloc[:,1].apply(lambda x: pd.to_numeric(str(x).strip().replace('\"',''), errors='coerce'))\n    # Standard: Enterococcus <=104. Failed if >104.\n    # Enterococcus numeric appears at columns that are 'Enterococcus' in header: typically last column of each tag pair.\n    # We will take all columns after col 4 that may contain numbers and infer by numeric parse.\n    # Approach: for each row, consider all columns from 5 onward; parse numeric tokens; if multiple, treat max? Better: take first numeric that is plausible.\n    enter_cols=list(range(5, data.shape[1]))\n    ent_vals=[]\n    for c in enter_cols:\n        ent_vals.append(data.iloc[:,c].apply(parse_enterococcus))\n    ent_matrix=pd.concat(ent_vals, axis=1)\n    # choose first non-nan per row\n    ent=np.nanmax(ent_matrix.to_numpy(), axis=1)\n    # For mis-split cases where tag/number are in separate columns, nanmax will pick number.\n    standard_met = ent <= 104\n    failed = ~standard_met\n    # rainfall within 24h means 1-Day Rain > 0. In preview sometimes 0.00\n    pos1 = rain1>0\n    failed_total += np.nansum(failed)\n    failed_and_pos1day += np.nansum(failed & pos1)\n\npct = (failed_and_pos1day/failed_total)*100 if failed_total else np.nan\nprint('failed_total',failed_total)\nprint('failed_and_pos1day',failed_and_pos1day)\nprint('pct',pct)\nprint(round(pct,2))"}) [toolUseId=call_tKFOrkBlWLgcRrANhxpMM3fx]
